item.title: [V2][AutoRenamed]317 deob, On demand enable, etc
item.dc:creator: @_Discardedx21 `Discardedx2`
item.description:
@_Discardedx21 wrote:

[quote=“Davidi2, post:7, topic:414760”]For some reason I have the idea you don’t understand what “Auto” renamed would be

Teaching the program to recognize the code for certain classes for this revision isn’t at all automatic, and probably isn’t even faster than just a quick refactor in an IDE. If that’s not what you did, please correct me[/quote]

yes it would be faster to do the renaming manually. but, zkm automatically renames all the fields corresponding to the class. for example say you had a class file under the name of

“Class123” which you renamed in your IDE, to “ACoolClass”

all occurances of that class would be named as, for example “aClass123_231” or so.

whereas since i renamed with my tool before renaming with zkm and excluded the renamed classes from my zkm rename script, i had done the class automatically named “ACoolClass” where all occurances were something along the lines of “aCoolClass221”, which is a lot easier to read imo. even though you should go rename the fields anyways, it’s a lot easier to understand the code with it renamed like this (imo)

item.dc:creator: @_Discardedx21 `Discardedx2`
item.description:
@_Discardedx21 wrote:

This deob has been automatically renamed by my auto renamer, and has all 73 class names in the 317 client renamed. I find it super easy to read, and for you developers out there, wheather you just want to study the 317 client or develop off it, i’m sure you will find that this is THE client to use.

I have not renamed any fields or methods manually (except the ones used in Client#renderViewport). I left those to do for yourselves so you guys can find out how stuff works, and maybe make some cool edits to your client (seeing as we all know you like to do that), without having all that previously added crud.
